### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

The Editor's Draft version of CSS Cascading and Inheritance Module Level 6 includes a new way to scope css to a specific component that's inspired by but lighter weight than shadow dom

https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@scope

It's supported in most browsers (all but Firefox, which has a flag for the in-dev support).

I think it would fit nicely with the design of CSS view encapsulation in Angular and using a proper feature would make it easier to debug issues in devtools than the current confusing randomized generated css selectors with Emulated mode. It would serve as a nice alternative for projects that can't use native shadow dom. I personally think shadow dom is severe overkill for most apps' components and should really only be used for components that need deep isolation.

### Proposed solution

`ViewEncapsulation.CSS_SCOPE`

```css
@scope ([_nghost-ng-c1255074413]) to ([_nghost_scope]) {
  // Users existing css with :host replaced with :scope
}
```

Or something like that. Maybe even:

```css
@scope (<value of `selector` from @Component/Directive definition>) to ([_nghost_scope]) {
  // Users existing css with :host replaced with :scope
}
```

